    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-03-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="167"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d167">
                <head>167. National Security Action Memorandum No. 324<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d167fn1">Source: Johnson Library, National Security File, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss> File, <gloss target="#t_NSAM1"
                            >NSAM</gloss> 324, Box 6. Secret. An attached March 9 note from
                            <persName corresp="#p_BFM1">Bator</persName> to <persName
                            corresp="#p_BMG2">Buddy</persName> reads: “If you think it appropriate,
                        would you sign?”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1965-03-09">March 9, 1965</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>Secretary of the Treasury</item>
                    <item>Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>Secretary of the Interior</item>
                    <item>Secretary of Agriculture</item>
                    <item>Secretary of Commerce</item>
                    <item>Secretary of Labor</item>
                    <item>Director of Central Intelligence</item>
                    <item>President, Export-Import Bank</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Special Presidential Committee on U.S. Trade Relations with Eastern
                        European Countries and the Soviet Union</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has appointed a Special Committee, under the Chairmanship of Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJI1">J. Irwin Miller</persName>, to examine U.S.
                    trade relations with the countries of Eastern Europe and the Soviet Union. The
                    Committee is to explore all aspects of the question of expanding peaceful trade
                    in support of the President’s policy of widening our relations with these
                    countries.</p>
                <p>In addition to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MJI1">Miller</persName>, the members of
                    the Committee are: <list>
                        <item>Mr. <persName>Eugene R. Black</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Mr. <persName>William Blackie</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Mr. <persName>George R. Brown</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Mr. <persName>Charles W. Engelhard, Jr.</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Mr. <persName>James B. Fisk</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Mr. <persName>Nathaniel Goldfinger</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Mr. <persName>Crawford Greenewalt</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Mr. <persName>William A. Hewitt</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Dr. <persName>Max F. Millikan</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Mr. <persName>Charles G. Mortimer</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Dr. <persName>Herman B. Wells</persName>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_FER1">Edward R. Fried</persName> will serve as
                    Executive Secretary to the Committee and will be on detail for this purpose.</p>
                <p>The list of members, other than Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MJI1"
                    >Miller</persName>, has not yet been announced and hence should be treated as
                    privileged.</p>
                <p>The Committee will rely on the Government for the preparation of material and
                    briefings. The President has asked that all agencies of the <pb facs="0519"
                        n="485" xml:id="pg_485"/> Government be prepared to assist the Committee in
                    carrying out its assignment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMG2">
                            <hi rend="strong">McGeorge Bundy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
